<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <title>PyTorch Compatibility Matrix — CUDA, ROCm, XPU &amp; CPU</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Find compatible combinations of PyTorch, Python, CUDA, ROCm and Intel XPU versions, minimum NVIDIA driver versions, supported AMD GPU architectures, and the matching pip install command.">
  <link rel="canonical" href="https://{{ domain }}/">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
  <link rel="icon" href="data:image/svg+xml,<svg xmlns=%22http://www.w3.org/2000/svg%22 viewBox=%220 0 100 100%22><text y=%22.9em%22 font-size=%2290%22>🔥</text></svg>">
</head>
<body>
<header>
  <h1>🔥 PyTorch Compatibility Matrix</h1>
  <p class="subtitle">
    Every official PyTorch build — CUDA, ROCm, Intel XPU and CPU — with the Python versions,
    platforms, minimum drivers and the exact <code>pip install</code> command.
  </p>
  <p class="meta">
    Data scraped automatically from
    <a href="https://download.pytorch.org/whl/torch/">download.pytorch.org</a>
    · last updated <time datetime="{{ generated_utc }}">{{ generated_utc }}</time>
    · {{ n_combos }} build combinations
    · <a href="https://github.com/DanielHou315/pytorch_compatibilities">source on GitHub</a>
  </p>
</header>

<main>
  <section class="filters" aria-label="Filters">
    <div class="filter">
      <label for="f-torch">PyTorch</label>
      <select id="f-torch"></select>
    </div>
    <div class="filter">
      <label for="f-accel">Accelerator</label>
      <select id="f-accel"></select>
    </div>
    <div class="filter">
      <label for="f-accel-ver">Accelerator version</label>
      <select id="f-accel-ver"></select>
    </div>
    <div class="filter">
      <label for="f-python">Python</label>
      <select id="f-python"></select>
    </div>
    <div class="filter">
      <label for="f-os">OS / Arch</label>
      <select id="f-os"></select>
    </div>
    <div class="filter">
      <label for="f-gpu">Your GPU (optional)</label>
      <select id="f-gpu"></select>
    </div>
    <button id="f-reset" type="button">Reset</button>
  </section>

  <p id="gpu-note" class="gpu-note" hidden></p>
  <p id="count" class="count" role="status"></p>

  <table id="results">
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>PyTorch</th>
        <th>Accelerator</th>
        <th>Python</th>
        <th>OS / Arch</th>
        <th>Requirements</th>
        <th>Install</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody></tbody>
  </table>

  <section class="notes">
    <h2>Notes</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Minimum driver</strong> for CUDA rows comes from the
        <a href="https://docs.nvidia.com/cuda/cuda-toolkit-release-notes/index.html">NVIDIA CUDA release notes</a>.
        Thanks to minor-version compatibility, a driver new enough for CUDA 11.x/12.x/13.x runs every toolkit of the same major version.</li>
      <li><strong>ROCm GPU lists</strong> are the architectures officially supported per
        <a href="https://rocm.docs.amd.com/projects/install-on-linux/en/latest/reference/system-requirements.html">AMD's documentation</a>;
        more consumer GPUs often work unofficially (e.g. via <code>HSA_OVERRIDE_GFX_VERSION</code>).</li>
      <li><strong>GPU filter</strong> compares against toolkit-level support — official wheels are sometimes built for fewer
        architectures (<code>TORCH_CUDA_ARCH_LIST</code>), so treat results as an upper bound and check with
        <code>torch.cuda.is_available()</code>.</li>
      <li><strong>macOS</strong> CPU wheels include MPS (Metal) acceleration on Apple Silicon for PyTorch ≥ 1.12.</li>
      <li><strong>NVIDIA Jetson</strong> (Xavier, Orin) is Linux aarch64 only and uses
        <a href="https://docs.nvidia.com/deeplearning/frameworks/install-pytorch-jetson-platform/index.html">NVIDIA's JetPack-specific wheels</a> —
        the aarch64 CUDA wheels here target SBSA servers (e.g. GH200).</li>
      <li><strong>Intel XPU</strong> wheels need <a href="https://www.intel.com/content/www/us/en/developer/articles/tool/pytorch-prerequisites-for-intel-gpu/2-9.html">Intel GPU drivers</a>.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</main>

<footer>
  <p>
    Built on the work of <a href="https://github.com/elenacliu/pytorch_cuda_driver_compatibilities">elenacliu/pytorch_cuda_driver_compatibilities</a> —
    thank you, <a href="https://github.com/elenacliu">@elenacliu</a>!
    Maintained by <a href="https://github.com/DanielHou315">Daniel Hou</a>. Updated daily by CI.
  </p>
</footer>

<script id="dataset" type="application/json">{{ dataset_json | safe }}</script>
<script src="app.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
